  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>The dwarven pelletbow is a crossbowlike weapon that is loaded with and fires&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/weapons/weapon-descriptions/sling\">sling</a>&nbsp;bullets rather than bolts.</em></p>\n<p>A dwarven light pelletbow can be reloaded as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Free-Actions\">free action</a>&nbsp;(allowing characters to attack with it multiple times in a round).</p>\n<p>Normally a pelletbow takes two hands to operate, but you can shoot (but not load) a pelletbow with one hand by taking a –2 penalty on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a>. You can shoot one pelletbow with each hand, but you take a penalty on attack rolls for attacking with two light weapons.</p>\n<p>Feats and special abilities that don’t involve proficiency (that don’t depend on dealing piercing damage or firing bolts) that apply to a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/equipment/weapons/weapon-descriptions/crossbow-light\">light crossbow</a>&nbsp;also apply to a dwarven light pelletbow.</p>",
